-- Three Dead After Gas Leak at Oil Refineries Plant, Israel Radio Reports
-- B y   C a l e v   B e n - D a v i d
-- 2010-11-24T05:35:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-24/three-dead-after-gas-leak-at-oil-refineries-plant-israel-radio-reports.html
Three workers have been killed and
at least seven injured from a leak of toxic gas at the Haifa,
Israel plant of Oil Refineries Ltd., Israel Radio reported.  Police are investigating the circumstances of the leak, Oil
Refineries Chief Executive Officer Yasher Ben-Morderchai told
Israel Radio. There is no immediate danger to the surrounding
area, Ben-Mordechai said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Calev Ben-David in Jerusalem at 
 cbendavid@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
